title: Opening Of a Password File
rule:
{'uuid': '1c6bd311-8f05-4188-bdbf-42d95b66536d', 'name': 'Opening Of a Password File', 'description': 'Command line detection of common office software opening some password related file. It could be a security breach if an unauthorized user access it.', 'severity': 30, 'type': 'correlation', 'pattern': 'detection:
  file_name:
    process.command_line|contains:
    - mdp
    - password
    - mot de passe
    - mots de passe
  process:
    process.name:
    - notepad.exe
    - winword.exe
    - excel.exe
    - powerpnt.exe
    - outlook.exe
  filter1:
    process.command_line|contains:
    - firefox.exe
    - msedge.exe
    - chrome.exe
    - Office16
  filter2:
    process.command_line|contains:
    - reset
    - forgot
    - "R\xE9initialiser"
  condition: file_name and process and not (filter1 and filter2)'}

title: Microsoft 365 Sign-in With No User Agent
rule:
{'uuid': 'd83325f1-e44b-4236-adbb-ff1cddedf26a', 'name': 'Microsoft 365 Sign-in With No User Agent', 'description': "Detects a sign-in without any User-Agent header. This may indicate that the sign-in originated from an adversary-in-the-middle phishing page or a password spraying tool. Sign-ins happening through a regular web browser always have a User-Agent header. Investigate the source IP address. If it is unknown, assume that the account's password is compromised.", 'severity': 75, 'type': 'correlation', 'pattern': "detection:
  sign_in:
    office365.auth.request_type:
    - Login:login
    - Cmsi:Cmsi
    - SAS:BeginAuth
    - SAS:EndAuth
    - SAS:ProcessAuth
    - Kmsi:kmsi
  failed:
    office365.logon_error:
    - InvalidUserNameOrPassword
    - InvalidPasswordNullPassword
    - IdsLocked
    - UserDisabled
  user_agent_present:
    user_agent.original: '*'
  condition: sign_in and not failed and not user_agent_present"}

title: Microsoft Defender XDR Office 365 Alert
rule:

    event.category: threat
  condition: selection'}

title: SEKOIA Intelligence Feed
rule: {'uuid': '399d4b62-cc5a-4645-b0f9-1849daf64a1e', 'name': 'SEKOIA Intelligence Feed', 'description': "Detect threats based on indicators of compromise (IOCs) collected by SEKOIA's Threat and Detection Research team.", 'severity': 60, 'type': 'cti', 'pattern': "[file:hashes.MD5 = '96a8b535b5e14b582ca5679a3e2a5946' OR file:hashes.'SHA-1' = 'f6b3577ea4b1a5641ae3421151a26268434c3db8' OR file:hashes.'SHA-256' = 'ab8f2217e59319b88080e052782e559a706fa4fb7b8b708f709ff3617124da89']"}

title: Microsoft Defender for Office 365 Low Severity AIR Alert Handled Automatically
rule:
{'uuid': '6fab6947-5cec-4241-97b3-8f4aba02ecf7', 'name': 'Microsoft Defender for Office 365 Low Severity AIR Alert Handled Automatically', 'description': 'Microsoft Defender for Office 365 includes the capability to run Automated investigation and response (AIR) actions. This rule detects when a Low or Informational severity alert triggered an automated investigation, and remediation was conducted automatically. Low and Informational alerts include when an email is reported by a user, or when a malicious email is removed after delivery.', 'severity': 30, 'type': 'correlation', 'pattern': 'detection:
  selection:
    service.name: AirInvestigation
    office365.investigation.alert.severity:
    - Low
    - Informational
    office365.investigation.status:
    - No threats found
    - Remediated
  condition: selection'}

title: CrowdStrike Falcon Intrusion Detection
rule:
{'uuid': 'cddb5f11-8bff-4070-b8cd-db3b28127a42', 'name': 'CrowdStrike Falcon Intrusion Detection', 'description': 'CrowdStrike Falcon agent raised an alert for an intrusion detection', 'severity': 80, 'type': 'correlation', 'pattern': 'detection:
  incident:
    crowdstrike.event_type: DetectionSummaryEvent
  vertex:
    crowdstrike.event_type: Vertex
  condition: incident or vertex'}

title: CrowdStrike Falcon Intrusion Detection Medium Severity
rule:

  incident:

    - Vertex
  severity:
